<LEADPARA>  Home: Forest of Philippines.; Habits: Agile climber. Eats shoots, buds,
flowers and fruit from many forest trees. Its main enemy is the Philippine
eagle, which feeds almost exclusively on flying lemurs.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Science &amp; Medicine  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  PHILIPPINE FLYING LEMUR
(CYNOCEPHALUS VOLANS)  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Creature Feature  </MEMO>
<TEXT>  Claim to fame: A membrane called the patagium stretches from neck to wrists,
ankles and tip of tail. It allows the lemur, which is about a foot long, to
glide through trees for up to 450 feet. The lemur is almost helpless on the
ground.  </TEXT>
